    Writing activity 05. Paragraphing
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <font size="4">The structure is stabilised in the cubic form at room temperature by doping with Y<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub> at about 8 mo1%. At higher levels the ionic conductivity of the overall electrolyte is reduced; lower levels confer insufficient cubic stability. Yttria is a good dopant because it is cheap, chemically stable under the operating conditions of the cell and in contact with the other components of the cell. The anode must be porous to allow the diffusion of gas. It must also be electronically conducting and have a comparable thermal expansion coefficient to the electrolyte. These parameters are met by deposition of nickel onto the YSZ structure, as illustrated in Fig. 4 below.</font> 
