        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">Which of these sources are unreliable?</font> 
    QUESTION 0 
        ANSWER: Gust, D., Moore, T.A., Moore, A.L. Mimicking Photosynthetic Solar Energy Transduction, Accounts of Chemical Research, 34, 40-48, 2001
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  This is a highly reliable source.  
        ANSWER: Br. Pat, 357 450, 1986
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  This is a reference to a patent, so will be reliable.
        ANSWER: www.skynewsonline.com
        FEEDBACK: News organisations are never reliable sources for academic essays.
        ANSWER: Catalytic Polymerization:  Facebook page.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  Facebook pages have no authority.  Posters are anonymous, so the Nobel Prize winner may actually be wee Jimmy from next door.
