INTRO <font size="4">Essay question:<br /><br />Does Hesiod have a consistent idea of justice? Discuss with reference to both <span style="font-style: italic;">Theogony</span> and <span style="font-style: italic;">Works and Days</span>.<br /><br />Sentence(s) from essay:<br /><br />Kronos was told by Heaven and Earth, who were his parents, that he would be killed and robbed of his throne by his son. This led him to eat his children until his wife, Rhea, fearful that he would devour his son Zeus, hid Zeus and gave Kronos a stone wrapped in a blanket to eat. Zeus then forced Kronos to regurgitate all the other children. <br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is this sentence description or argument?
        ANSWER: Description.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  We are just being told the story.  You need to use elements in the story to illustrate or underpin your argument.  Simply telling the story itself is never appropriate in an academic essay.
        ANSWER: Argument.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  We are just being told the story.  You need to use elements in the story to illustrate or underpin your argument.  Simply telling the story itself is never appropriate in an academic essay.
