        FEEDBACK: Not 1.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 2. 
        FEEDBACK: Not 2.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 3.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  The information is to enable your reader to locate the source quickly and easily.  We don't need to know that Catharine Edwards also wrote the introduction and notes.  We just need her name, the date and the publisher.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO  <font size="4">Bibliography:<br /><br />1. </font><font size="4">Lyne, </font><font size="4">R. O. A. M. </font><font size="4">(1988) '</font><font size="4">Augustan Poetry and Society' in </font><font size="4">J. Boardman, J. Griffin and O. Murray (eds.) </font><font size="4"><span style="font-style: italic;">The Oxford History of the Roman World,</span> (Oxford University Press)<br /><br /></font><font size="4">2. The Oxford History of the Roman World, Augustan Poetry and Society, R.O.A.M. Lyne, edited by J. Boardman J. Griffin and O. Murray, Oxford University Press, England, 1988.<br /><br /></font><font size="4">3. </font><font size="4">Boardman, J., Griffin. J. and Murray</font><font size="4">, O., The Oxford History of the Roman World, 'Augustan Poetry and Society' by R.O.A.M Lyne, edited by Oxford University Press, 1988.</font><br /> 
    QUESTION 0 Which of these entries is properly formatted for a bibliography?
        ANSWER: 1.
        FEEDBACK: That's correct.  We need author, date, name of article, name(s) of editors, name of book or journal, place of publication.
        ANSWER: 2.
        FEEDBACK: Not 2.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 3.
