        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO 1. Leading him into the underworld, Aeneas is afraid of the Sibyl.<br />2. Aeneas is afraid of the Sibyl leading him into the underworld.<br /> 
    QUESTION 0 Which sentence is an example of a dangling participle?
        ANSWER: 1.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  As written here, the sentence has Aeneas leading the Sibyl into the underworld, when it is the other way round.
        ANSWER: 2.
        FEEDBACK: No, that's not right.  Sentence 1 is an example of a dangling participle.  As written here, Aeneas is leading the Sibyl into the underworld, when, in fact, it's the other way round.
        Task freetext difficulty 3
