INTRO <font size="4">The proliferation of the <span style="font-style: italic;">internet </span>has fundamentally changed people's way of communicating. It has also altered what we think of as <span style="font-style: italic;">traditional society</span>. Yet human beings are still rooted in the notion of trade, although now they gather together in <span style="font-style: italic;">e-society</span> over the web. There are many examples of <span style="font-style: italic;">e-marketplaces</span>: Amazon, ebay, and all shops with on-line facilities. As Mary Smith says in The History of Marketing, <span style="font-style: italic;">'E-commerce</span> is here to stay'.<sup>1</sup> <br /><br />Footnote reads:<br /><br />Mary Smith, '<span style="font-style: italic;">Modern Markets</span>' in The History of Marketing (London: A. Publisher, 2004) p.109<br /></font> 
