me:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-priority:99;	mso-style-qformat:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}</style><![endif]-->
<p><font size="4"> Government makes such decisions to take account of security issues, neutralise any threats and for findings to decide on criminal but on the other hand it is interestingly controversial when it backfires including those parliament members the decision makers of the policies' who also think like a common people at some point especially when they realise that their conversations across telephone will be disclosed to third party for security reasons. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0  <link href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml" rel="File-List" /><link href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_themedata.thmx" rel="themeData" /><link href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_colorschememapping.xml" rel="colorSchemeMapping" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false EN-GB X-NONE X-NONE MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style> &lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:&quot;Cambria Math&quot;; panose-1:2 4 5 3 5 4 6 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:roman; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1107304683 0 0 159 0;} @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-unhide:no; mso-style-qformat:yes; mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;} .MsoChpDefault {mso-style-type:export-only; mso-default-props:yes; font-size:10.0pt; mso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;} @page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;} div.Section1 {page:Section1;} --&gt; </style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-priority:99;	mso-style-qformat:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">This is a really long sentence that doesn't make much sense. From the options offered, click on the one you think best reflects the writer's main point. Each option has an explanation. </font></p> 
        ANSWER: A government makes decisions that backfire.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. The writer seems to be saying that the government makes decisions that may become controversial if they backfire (i.e. if those decisions affect members of the parliament).
        ANSWER: Governments controversially think like common people.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. The policies, not governments, are controversial, although members of parliament may well think like 'common people'. 
        ANSWER: A government has to make decisions on security issues and threats, and its members will be affected by the decisions made, such as telephone conversations being recorded.
        FEEDBACK: Correct. 
        ANSWER: Common people make decisions about telephone conversations.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. Although this is indirectly what the writer is saying, it's not the key meaning of the sentence.
        Task freetext difficulty 3
