        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <font size="4">The purpose of implanting microchips into children's bodies is to make them easier to identify.</font> 
    QUESTION 0 This sentence is ambiguous.  How?
        ANSWER: It's not clear what the purpose of microchipping is.
        FEEDBACK: No - that's not where the ambiguity arises.
        ANSWER: It's not clear who is needing to be identified:  the microchips or the children.
        FEEDBACK: Quite right.  Microchips are the subject of the sentence, so when we meet the word 'them', we automatically feel it refers to microchips, although the writer means 'them' to refer to children.
    QUESTION 1 How can this problem be rectified?
        ANSWER: It can't be rectified:  we just have to assume readers are intelligent enough to make proper sense of the sentence.
        FEEDBACK: No, we can rectify the problem - and no matter how intelligent the reader is, he or she should not be required to make proper sense of the sentence.  Making proper sense of the sentence is the writer's responsibility.
        ANSWER: It can be rectified by inserting the correct subject (children) near the verb (to identify).
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  The sentence would then read:  The purpose of implanting microchips into children's bodies is to make children easier to identify.
    Writing activity 03. Punctuation - apostrophes
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <font size="4">Many people will copy a CD for a friend, rip a friends DVD to their computer, buy pirate CDs, DVDs and games, and think nothing of it.</font><br />
    QUESTION 0 There is an apostrophe missing from this sentence - which of the following words is the correct one?
        ANSWER: friend's
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  The apostrophe is used here to indicate that the DVD belongs to a friend.
        ANSWER: friends'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  The apostrophe here indicates that the DVD belongs to several friends, but we know it only belongs to one: 'a friend'.
        ANSWER: CD's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  Apostrophes are never used to form plurals. Making an acronym or abbreviation plural can be hard because not using an apostrophe may look weird.  However, weird or not, no apostrophe is needed!
        ANSWER: DVD's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  An apostrophe is never used to make a plural. Click on the blue question mark above the exercises for more information.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C06%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">By adding a postage fee, marketers that are currently dropping several unsolicited messages into users inboxes may have to rediscover the value of segmentation and targeting. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 An apostrophe is needed in the phrase 'users inboxes' to demonstrate that the inboxes belong to more than one user. Which of the following options is correct?
        ANSWER: user's inboxes
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  This means that the inboxes belong to only one user.
        ANSWER: users inboxe's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  We're looking for an apostrophe to indicate to whom the inboxes belong.  In addition, 'inboxes' is a plain plural and plain plurals never need apostrophes.
        ANSWER: users' inboxes
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  Here, the apostrophe signals that the inboxes belong to all the users.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C02%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">Some argue that it is an invasion of a persons' privacy to listen in on another persons' telephone call, whereas others argue that it is necessary for the protection of society. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 There are two apostrophe errors in this sentence. Choose the corrected words from the options provided below.
        ANSWER: person's (first instance), other's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - 'others' is a plural here so does not need an apostrophe.
        ANSWER: person's (second instance), others'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - others is a plural here, but not possessive, so does not need an apostrophe.
        ANSWER: person's (first instance), person's (second instance)
        FEEDBACK: Correct - 'person' is singular, so the apostrophe must come before the 's' that makes it a possessive (the privacy of the person; the telephone call of another person).
        ANSWER: persons's (first instance), persons's (second instance)
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - 'person' is singular here so doesn't need an 's' before the apostrophe.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
