<p> <font size="4">More than half of the worlds email traffic is spam. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 One word in this sentence needs an apostrophe. Which of the options below is correct?
        ANSWER: worlds'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  The writer is referring to one world, but this apostrophe indicates many worlds. 
        ANSWER: e'mail
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  Email is fine as it is. Apostrophes are used to indicate contraction, but email (or e-mail) is the standard shortening of 'electronic mail'.
        ANSWER: world's
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  This apostrophe shows that the writer is referring to one world. 
        ANSWER: 'spam
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  There is no need for an apostrophe here as no letters have been removed from the beginning of the word.
