<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span><font size="4">Its up to us to opt for the option that suit's one's situation best.</font><o:p></o:p></span></p> 
    QUESTION 0 There are two apostrophe errors in this sentence. Choose the corrected words from the options provided below.
        ANSWER: It's, ones
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - one of these is right!
        ANSWER: suits, ones
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - one of these choices is correct!
        ANSWER: It's, suits
        FEEDBACK: Correct - 'Its' needs to 'it's', which is a shortening of 'it is'. 'Suit's' needs to be 'suits' as it is a form of the verb 'to suit'.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <link href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C11%5Cclip_filelist.xml" rel="File-List" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">Despite our imaginary societies views on this matter, the technology required to commit such an act exists and is readily available. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 There is an apostrophe error in the sentence. Which word is affected?
        ANSWER: views
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  'Views' is a plain plural and does not need an apostrophe.  Click on the blue question mark above the exercises to remind yourself of the rules.
        ANSWER: societies
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  Now answer the next question below.
        ANSWER: exists
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  'Exists' is a verb and so does not need an apostrophe.  Click on the blue question mark above the exercises to remind yourself of the rules.
    QUESTION 1 What should the affected word be changed to?
        ANSWER: societies'
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  This is a possessive plural, so needs an apostrophe after the final 's'
        ANSWER: societie's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  Even if we were talking about a single society instead of many societies, the singular of society is 'society', not 'societie'
        ANSWER: society's
        FEEDBACK: This could be correct if the writer was talking about one society.  Actually, in the context of the essay, the writer was talking of many societies, so the apostrophe should, in this case, come after the final 's':  societies' 
        ANSWER: societys'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.   We need the proper plural spelling, then a possessive apostrophe.  Press the blue question mark for further explanation and examples.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
