<p> <font size="4">I feel that the biggest justification for allowing phone tapping by the government, comes from the preventative measures it can achieve, in the fight to ensure public safety. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 There are two commas in this sentence. Do you think there should be?
        ANSWER: Yes
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - the sentence could have one comma, after achieve, although this isn't really necessary.
        ANSWER: No
        FEEDBACK: Correct - the sentence could have one comma, after achieve, although this isn't really necessary.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C07%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p><font size="4"> It is possible to assume that at some stage e-societies may even become equally important, as the societies, in which we live today. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 What would you do with the commas in this sentence?
        ANSWER: leave them where they are
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - these commas break up the sentence, making it hard to read and understand.
        ANSWER: keep the first one, delete the second one
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - the first comma inserts a break between 'important' and 'as', which need to be together in order for the phrase to make sense - what is 'equally important' as e-societies?
        ANSWER: remove both
        FEEDBACK: Correct - this sentence doesn't need any commas; it's easiest to understand without them.
        ANSWER: delete the first one, keep the second one
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - the first second inserts a break between 'societies' and 'in which we live today', which need to be together in order for the phrase to make sense - it must be clear which societies are being talked about.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
