<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span><font size="4">I think that because the amount charged to users would be less than, say ten pence, it is not enough to punish the people who spam and abuse the system.</font><o:p></o:p></span></p> 
    QUESTION 0 Which of the following alternatives do you think works best?
        ANSWER: I think that, because the amount charged to users would be less than say ten pence, it is not enough to punish the people who spam and abuse the system.
        FEEDBACK: Possible. This option is feasible - if you take out the words between the two commas, the sentence does make sense, but it feels as if information is missing. 'I think that it is not enough to punish the people who spam and abuse the system.' Therefore, the words between the commas are crucial to the reader's understanding of the sentence (and thus the argument).
        ANSWER: I think that because the amount charged to users would be less than, say, ten pence it is not enough to punish the people who spam and abuse the system. 
        FEEDBACK: Correct. This option works well - taking out the word encased by commas doesn't affect the meaning at all. That word only shows that the ten pence is a suggestion, which is not absolutely crucial to the reader's understanding of the sentence.
        ANSWER: I think that because the amount charged to users, would be less than say ten pence, it is not enough to punish the people who spam and abuse the system.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. If you remove the words between the commas, the sentence does not make sense: 'I think that because the amount charged to users it is not enough to punish the people who spam and abuse the system.'
        ANSWER: I think that because the amount charged to users would be less than, say ten pence it is not enough to punish, the people who spam and abuse the system.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. If you remove the words between the commas, the sentence does not make sense: 'I think that because the amount charged to users would be less than the people who spam and abuse the system.'
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
