<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;"><span><font size="4">One such change, is the move from traditional social methods to that of the on-line community.</font><o:p></o:p></span></p> 
    QUESTION 0 Should the comma in this sentence be...?
        ANSWER: left where it is
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. The comma should not be left where it is - it interrupts the sentence unnecessarily here. 
        ANSWER: moved to after 'move'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. It is important to keep 'move from traditional social methods' together so that no meaning is lost.
        ANSWER: removed
        FEEDBACK: Correct. There is no need for a comma in this sentence at all - it is grammatically correct, and it makes sense, without a comma.
        ANSWER: replaced with a colon
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. A colon is used to indicate that more information about what precedes it will follow after it - this certainly wouldn't be the case here.
    Writing activity 07. Punctuation - dashes
