        Task wordclick difficulty 3
    Writing activity 05. Punctuation - semi-colons
        Task freetext difficulty 3
        Task freetext difficulty 2
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO For instance, as reported in <span style="font-style: italic;">Metro </span>on 18 November 2008; a list of 10,000 members of the British National Party was published on the internet and members' privacy was compromised. 
    QUESTION 0 In this sentence, a semi-colon has been used. Would you change it to something else?
        ANSWER: No - it's fine as it is 
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - semi-colons are used to break up two related sentences, but here it's just interrupting one sentence.
        ANSWER: Yes - a full stop
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. If you did that, you would have two sentences - the first of which wouldn't make any sense.
        ANSWER: Yes - a colon
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. A colon is used to introduce a list or an additional piece of information.
        ANSWER: Yes - a comma
        FEEDBACK: Correct - a comma means that 'as reports in Metro on 18 November 2008' becomes a distinct clause within the sentence. It could be removed and the meaning of the sentence would not be changed.
        Task freetext difficulty 2
        Task freetext difficulty 2
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C13%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:Calibri; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">The question then arises; will we become more dependent on the internet? </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 The semi-colon has been used incorrectly in this sentence. Which do you think is the best alternative?
        ANSWER: The question then arises. Will we become more dependent on the internet?
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - in this context, this new first sentence doesn't really make any sense.
        ANSWER: The question then arises: will we become more dependent on the internet?
        FEEDBACK: Correct - here a colon works really well. It indicates that what comes after the colon will be the question that has arisen.
        ANSWER: The question then arises, will we become more dependent on the internet?
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - the comma doesn't lead into the question as neatly as another punctuation mark would.
        ANSWER: The question then arises - will we become more dependent on the internet?
        FEEDBACK: Possible. The dash can be used in this way - to lead to more information. It's maybe not the 'best' punctuation mark to use, but it does work reasonably well here.
        Task freetext difficulty 2
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><link rel="themeData" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_themedata.thmx" /><link rel="colorSchemeMapping" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_colorschememapping.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false EN-GB X-NONE X-NONE MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style> &lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:&quot;Cambria Math&quot;; panose-1:2 4 5 3 5 4 6 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:roman; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1107304683 0 0 159 0;} @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-unhide:no; mso-style-qformat:yes; mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;} .MsoChpDefault {mso-style-type:export-only; mso-default-props:yes; font-size:10.0pt; mso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;} @page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;} div.Section1 {page:Section1;} --&gt; </style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-priority:99;	mso-style-qformat:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">The existence of a perfect clique, described above as a communication network, becomes less possible as the number of people in a group explodes, nevertheless, modern societies do rely heavily on non-face-to-face or other indirect means of communication. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 This sentence is essentially two whole sentences put together - a semi-colon could be used to break the sentence appropriately. Where would you put the semi-colon?
        ANSWER: after 'clique', replacing the comma
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. Replacing that comma would break the sentence too soon - the first segment needs to remain linked to 'becomes less possible...'
        ANSWER: after 'explodes', replacing the comma
        FEEDBACK: Correct. Replacing that comma with a semi-colon would neatly break the sentences into two parts, with the second sentence leading on naturally from the first.
        ANSWER: after 'nevertheless', replacing the comma
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. Replacing that comma would make it unclear what the 'nevertheless' relates to - it doesn't really fit in with what would become the first part.
        ANSWER: after 'non-face-to-face'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. This would still leave the main two parts of the sentence unbroken, would make it unclear what 'non-face-to-face' refers to, and would leave 'or other indirect means of communication' out on a limb.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><link rel="themeData" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_themedata.thmx" /><link rel="colorSchemeMapping" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtmlclip1%5C01%5Cclip_colorschememapping.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false EN-GB X-NONE X-NONE MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style> &lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */ @font-face {font-family:&quot;Cambria Math&quot;; panose-1:2 4 5 3 5 4 6 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:roman; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1107304683 0 0 159 0;} @font-face {font-family:Calibri; panose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:swiss; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:-1610611985 1073750139 0 0 159 0;} /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-unhide:no; mso-style-qformat:yes; mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:10.0pt; margin-left:0cm; line-height:115%; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:11.0pt; font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-US; mso-fareast-language:EN-US; mso-bidi-language:EN-US;} .MsoChpDefault {mso-style-type:export-only; mso-default-props:yes; font-size:10.0pt; mso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt; mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;} @page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;} div.Section1 {page:Section1;} --&gt; </style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-priority:99;	mso-style-qformat:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";}</style><![endif]-->
<p> <font size="4">Indeed, it is used by many users as an alternative to society; A separate realm for escape. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 What in this sentence needs to be changed?
        ANSWER: Nothing
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - the sentence should not stay as it is.
        ANSWER: the semi-colon needs to be changed to a colon
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - that wouldn't rectify the issues with this sentence.
        ANSWER: the 'A' after the semi-colon should be lower case
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - that wouldn't rectify the issues with this sentence
        ANSWER: the semi-colon needs to be change to a colon AND the 'A' after the semi-colon should be lower case.
        FEEDBACK: Correct - both these things need to be changed to make the sentence acceptable. Capital letters never appear after a colon or semi-colon (unless the word is a proper or brand name). Also, as the text that follows the semi-colon doesn't form a complete sentence (it just provides a small piece of extra information), the semi-colon should be changed to a colon.
    Writing activity 29. Structure - concluding lines
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <font size="4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Essay title: </span><br /><br />Suppose a society holds that it is wrong for one individual to eavesdrop on the telephone conversations of another citizen. Should that society also prohibit the government from listening in on its citizens' telephone conversations? </font>
