<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4" style="font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Read the following essay title and then the concluding line(s) that are offered. Choose the concluding line(s) you think best. Each selection has an explanation, so even if your choice agrees with ours, it is worth browsing through them all.</font><o:p></o:p></p> <!--EndFragment--> 
        ANSWER: It is everybody's right to go to university.  Universities are the sign of a civilised country.  Sometimes the funding puts people off but it did not put me off.   Ministers should look at that.   
        FEEDBACK: The thoughts in these lines are fine in themselves, but they do not finish the essay off.  Nor would a reader be able to say for certain what the title was.  It could have been:  What puts people off going to university?
        ANSWER: In conclusion, I chose to go to university because I want to increase my stock of knowledge, meet new people and improve my social skills. 
        FEEDBACK: This concluding line is the best because although it may be dull, it appears to draw together the themes of the essay and answers the question directly.  
        ANSWER: The university is a strange place.  It is not at all as I expected.
        FEEDBACK: These lines have wandered off the point.  Could you tell what the essay question was?  No - nor could I.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file://localhost/Users/katiegrant/Library/Caches/TemporaryItems/msoclip1/01/clip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 0 1 55 319 2 1 391 11.1282 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> 0 0 0 </xml><![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */@font-face {font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; panose-1:0 2 2 6 3 5 4 5 2 3; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:auto; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:50331648 0 0 0 1 0;} /* Style Definitions */p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:12.0pt; font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;}table.MsoNormalTable {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; font-size:10.0pt; font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--StartFragment-->
<p><font size="4"><strong>Essay title:</strong><br /></font> </p>
<p><font size="4">Human beings have lived in societies of various kinds throughout their existence. Identify key characteristics of traditional societies and then show how well or poorly these characteristics are emulated in the 'society' of the internet. Do you think that we will become ever more dependent on our electronic society? In your view, how far can such a society be taken? </font></p><!--EndFragment--> 
