<p> <font size="4">If we consider that every preceding generation is being introduced to computers at an early age, it is fair to say that the majority of the planet will be computer literate to some degree. </font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 Which word has been used incorrectly in this sentence?
        ANSWER: generation
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - 'generation' is fine here.
        ANSWER: planet
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - 'planet' is fine here.
        ANSWER: computer literate
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - 'computer literate' is fine here.
        ANSWER: preceding
        FEEDBACK: Correct - 'preceding' means 'coming before' so is incorrect in this context as not all previous generations were introduced to computers at an early age.
    QUESTION 1 Which word should be used instead?
        ANSWER: following
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this carries the right sense but is not quite the right word.
        ANSWER: other
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this doesn't convey the author's meaning.
        ANSWER: succeeding
        FEEDBACK: Correct - succeeding means everything coming after, which is what the author wants to say.
        ANSWER: past
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this doesn't convey the author's meaning at all - precisely the opposite, in fact.
        Task wordclick difficulty 1
