    Writing activity 20. colons and semi-colons
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <font size="4">Component reliability in Formula One is affected by two main factors; car performance and driver safety.</font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is the semi-colon in this sentence correctly used?
        ANSWER: Yes.  It divides up the sentence nicely.
        FEEDBACK: The semi-colon is not correctly used here.   A colon should be used to introduce a list, even if the list only has two components.
        ANSWER: No.  It's not the correct form of punctuation here.
        FEEDBACK: Quite right.  The semi-colon is not correctly used here.   A colon should be used to introduce a list, even if the list has only two components.
        ANSWER: It doesn't really matter.
        FEEDBACK: I'm afraid it does matter.  Incorrect punctuation can alter the meaning of a sentence.  Correct punctuation clarifies your text and impresses your marker.  The semi-colon here should be a colon.  A colon should be used to introduce a list, even if the list has only two components.
