        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
INTRO <font size="4">A helicopter is a frame, propelled by a fan that needs to be powerful enough to support the weight of the frame. Since the materials from which a helicopter is made are very stiff, the main problem is excessive vibration. These vibrations are of different types: imposed vibration; self-exited vibration; bearing whirl; flow excitation from working fluid; rotating friction; unsymmetrical rotor; and synchronous whirl set up by interaction between transverse and torsional modes of vibration. There are different ways of monitoring vibrations, and this project looks at different methods of control or repair. The simplest method of repair would be to replace all the parts that had begun to vibrate. This method has some advantages. There is also a Rotor Track and Balance (RTB) system for adjusting the blades, though this is very labour intensive and costly. Health and Usage Monitoring Systems (HUMS) can detect problems in the drive train, engines, oil system, and track and balance functions for the rotor system.</font><br />
