INTRO <font size="4">Several initial thoughts turned out to be wildly incorrect and we made new models to keep the ball rolling.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is this sentence formal enough for a report?
        ANSWER: Yes.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        ANSWER: No.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  I don't think either 'wildly' or 'to keep the ball rolling' have any place in a formal report.  Try:  'Wrong assumptions were made at the start of the project and new models were constructed'.    That's all we need.  Everything else is superfluous.
