<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 7.5pt;">Acknowledgment: these examples and styles are taken or adapted for teaching purposes from Weissberg and Buker (1990) <i>Writing up Results</i></span></p> <!--EndFragment--> <br /> 
    QUESTION 0 Which of these statements shows findings limited to one report?
        ANSWER: 1.
        FEEDBACK: No, not this one.  This is a statement of ongoing fact.  This is shown by use of the present tense:  Nutrient resorption IS a common ...
        ANSWER: 2.  
        FEEDBACK: No, not this one.  Here we are not given the results.  We are simply told that studies have been carried out.  The use of the past perfect tense - HAVE STUDIED - tells us that the studies referred to have been completed.  
        ANSWER: 3.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  The use of the past tense - ALLOCATED - to report the findings shows that these findings are limited to Allington's study.  If the results were accepted as ongoing fact, the present tense would be used:  teachers ALLOCATE ...
