INTRO <font size="4">Due to a number of setbacks, the team felt there were a lot of areas in the main design of the project that could be enhanced by future work. The first piece of work would be to conduct more testing on the final test board. At the time of writing, we are still unaware of the problems that might exist with the final board. Therefore, in order for any improvements to be made to the board, the stability of the current board has to be ensured first.<br /><br />As well as this, future designers would need to optimise the area of the PCB in order to mount the system in the steering wheel. This may require the sub-systems to be divided across multiple boards with appropriate inter-board connections. <br /><br />Optimising the storage of graphics in the Microcontroller's FLASH would be useful, although it was recognised that an external FLASH would currently slow the system. Work should be done on this. <br /><br />A specialised microcontroller would cut down on the number of devices required. <br /></font> 
