        FEEDBACK: I would say 'nearly' rather than 'yes'.  Colloquialisms have crept in, for example 'a lot of areas'.  What is 'a lot'? But the text improves as it continues.  Being concise, as in the last two items, is always commendable.
        ANSWER: No.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree, although I would say the tone of the text is nearly right rather than absolutely right.   Colloquialisms have crept in, for example 'a lot of areas'.  What is 'a lot'? But the text improves as it continues.  Being concise, as in the last two items, is always commendable.
    QUESTION 1 Does it inspire confidence that the final test board had not been tested?
        ANSWER: That doesn't matter.  It can be tested in the future.
