        ANSWER: 7.
        FEEDBACK: Well done.  That's correct.  Waller needs a date and the other references should come after each of the 'variables' listed, e.g. authoritarian-democratic (Lewin, Lippett
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <font size="4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Appendix A</span><br /><br />References<br /><br />Figure 1 referenced from MicroChip Technology Inc. Tom Perme, AN1101, Page 1, Figure 1, Capacitive Illustrations, 2007.<br /><br />Figure 2 Table of Dielectric Constants, http://hyperphysics.phyastr.gsu.edu/hbase/tables/diel/html [21.03.09]<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 What is the matter with these references?
        ANSWER: They are formatted wrongly.
        FEEDBACK: No, that's not it.  Try again.
        ANSWER: An appendix is not the right place for references.
        FEEDBACK: Quite right.  References go in their own section.  That's only half the story, though.
        ANSWER: An appendix is not the right place for references and figures do not come under 'references'.
        FEEDBACK: That's correct.  Appendices and references are different things;  and if such a list is required, figures should be listed under a section headed List of Figures.  Figures must also be clearly labeled when they appear in the text itself.
