<![endif]--><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: "times new roman";">Although Janes faith is undefined, she is surrounded by individuals of different beliefs and extremes of those beliefs.</span> 
    QUESTION 0 There is an apostrophe error in this sentence - which of the following do you think is the correct version of the word that currently contains the error?
        ANSWER: belief's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this is the plural of belief: apostrophes are never used to indicate plurals.
        ANSWER: extremes'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this is the plural form of extreme, and does not need a possessive apostrophe (which this one is) - the extremes aren't possessing anything in this sentence.
        ANSWER: individual's
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this is the plural of individual: apostrophes are never required to make a plural.
        ANSWER: Janes'
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - there's only one Jane, whereas this suggests that there are lots of Janes with an undefined faith.
        ANSWER: Jane's
        FEEDBACK: Correct - there is one Jane who possesses an undefined faith, so the apostrophe is essential here. For more information on how to use apostrophes, click on the blue question mark near the top of the page.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
