    Writing activity 02. Punctuation - colons
        Task freetext difficulty 2
        Task freetext difficulty 3
        Task freetext difficulty 1
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C02%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:12.0pt; font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p><font size="4">Overall Hamlet is very influenced by the anticipation of his uncle's death, It is something which he wants to control.</font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 This sentence is badly punctuated - a colon can be used to make it a lot easier to read. Which of the following options do you think works best?
        ANSWER: Overall: Hamlet is very influenced by the anticipation of his uncle's death, It is something which he wants to control.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - the colon shouldn't be put here. A colon is used to introduce more information, or a list.
        ANSWER: Overall Hamlet is very influenced by the anticipation of his uncle's death, It is something: which he wants to control.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - a colon should not be put here. A colon is used to introduce more information or a list. What goes before should be a complete sentence; what follows can be a fragment or a complete sentence.
        ANSWER: Overall Hamlet is very influenced by the anticipation of his uncle's death: it is something which he wants to control.
        FEEDBACK: Correct - here the colon is being used to provide more information about why Hamlet is influenced by this anticipation. Also note that the capital letter on 'It' has been made lower case - this is the preferred style in British English. American English prefers the capital letter after a colon.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO  <link rel="File-List" href="file:///C:%5CDOCUME%7E1%5CABI-PE%7E1%5CLOCALS%7E1%5CTemp%5Cmsohtml1%5C03%5Cclip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]> <![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Style Definitions */ p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:12.0pt; font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--[if gte mso 10]><style> /* Style Definitions */ table.MsoNormalTable	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;	mso-style-noshow:yes;	mso-style-parent:"";	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;	mso-para-margin:0cm;	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;	font-size:10.0pt;	font-family:"Times New Roman";	mso-ansi-language:#0400;	mso-fareast-language:#0400;	mso-bidi-language:#0400;}</style><![endif]-->
<p><font size="4">Like Herbert, he makes the distinction between the body and the soul - whilst 'our best men with thee do go', their bones remain and their soul is delivered to heaven.</font></p> 
    QUESTION 0 This sentence works quite well with a dash, but one of the following options works better - which one?
        ANSWER: Like Herbert, he makes the distinction between the body and the soul: whilst 'our best men with thee do go', their bones remain and their soul is delivered to heaven.
        FEEDBACK: Correct - putting the colon here means that how he makes the distinction follows nearly on from the statement that he makes the distinction.
        ANSWER: Like Herbert, he makes the distinction between the body and the soul; whilst 'our best men with thee do go', their bones remain and their soul is delivered to heaven.
        FEEDBACK: Possibly - the semi-colon works reasonably well here. It links two closely-related sentences, but perhaps does not indicate that the second explains the first.
        ANSWER: Like Herbert, he makes the distinction between the body and the soul. Whilst 'our best men with thee do go', their bones remain and their soul is delivered to heaven.
        FEEDBACK: Probable - the full stop could be used here, but it does provide a very definite break. The natural flow encouraged by a different punctuation mark might be preferable.
