<p>These include; moral rules on how to live life the way God wants, a sense of humility before the God who creates man, a highlighting of human weakness as they fall victim to sinfulness, the sense of comfort or hope from God in difficult times and finally the promise of eternal life.</p> 
    QUESTION 0 The punctuation in this sentence needs to be changed in order for the sentence to be easier to read and understand. Which of the following changes do you think is best?
        ANSWER: change the semi-colon to a colon; change all the commas to semi-colons, insert a semi-colon after 'times'
        FEEDBACK: Correct - this changes will make the sentence more obviously a list, with the semi-colons clearly separating each item in the list.
        ANSWER: No changes
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - some changes are needed to make it clear that this is a list.
        ANSWER: Change the semi-colon to a comma
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - this would make the sentence more confusing. It's necessary to change the punctuation marks throughout the sentence in order to demonstrate that this is a list.
