<p>These include; moral rules on how to live life the way God wants, a sense of humility before the God who creates man, a highlighting of human weakness as they fall victim to sinfulness, the sense of comfort or hope from God in difficult times and finally the promise of eternal life.</p> 
    QUESTION 0 The semi-colon in this sentence has been misused - semi-colons can be used to separate items in a list, but should not introduce a list. What would you change the semi-colon to?
        ANSWER: comma
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - commas never introduce lists, but they can separate items in a list.
        ANSWER: full stop
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - definitely not. A full stop here would result in two incomplete sentences that don't make much sense.
        ANSWER: colon
        FEEDBACK: Correct - a colon can be used here to demonstrate that a list of things is about to follow.
        ANSWER: apostrophe
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect - an apostrophe would be a very random choice here, as apostrophes are used to indicate possession or missing letters. They punctuate words rather than sentences.
