<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN-US"><font size="4">In his essay entitled 'The Evolving American Dream', which takes as its focus F. Scott Fitzgerald's novels 'Tender Is The Night' and <i>The Last Tycoon</i>, John F. Callahan states that, &quot;Fitzgerald embodies in his tissues ... the fluid polarities of American experience<sup>1</sup>.&quot; </font><o:p></o:p></span></p> <!--EndFragment--> 
    QUESTION 0 Which is the correct way to format a book title: enclosed in quotation marks or in italics?
        ANSWER: Enclosed in quotation marks.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  Book and journal titles are italicised, and essay or article titles are enclosed within quotation marks. 
        ANSWER: In italics.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  Book and journal titles are italicised, and essay or article titles are enclosed within quotation marks.
    QUESTION 1 Should the quotation marks that are properly used in this example be single or double?
        ANSWER: Double.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  Double quotation marks are reserved for quotations within quotations.  Quotation marks should normally be single.
        ANSWER: Single.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  Double quotation marks are used for quotations within quotations only.
    QUESTION 2 Is the footnote number in this example properly placed?
        ANSWER: No.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  The footnote number comes after the final punctuation, i.e. in this case after the full stop.
        ANSWER: Yes.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  The footnote number comes after the final punctuation, i.e. in this case after the full stop.
    QUESTION 3 Are the closing quotation marks of the Callahan quote properly placed?
        ANSWER: Yes.
        FEEDBACK: No, they're not.  When a quote is part of a bigger sentence, as in this case, the closing quotation marks (which should be single quotation marks) come before the full stop.
        ANSWER: No.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  When a quote is part of a bigger sentence, as in this case, the closing quotation marks (which should be single quotation marks) come before the full stop.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
