<p> <font size="4">Pope, Alexander, in <i>The Norton Anthology of English Literature</i>, ed. by M. Abrams, 6<sup>th</sup> edn, 2 vols, (New York: Norton &amp; Co. Ltd.) vol. 1., pp.2212-2295 </font></p><!--EndFragment--> 
    QUESTION 0 What is wrong with this bibliographical entry?
        ANSWER: There's too much information.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  You should give all the information you can.
        ANSWER: Some information is missing.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  I'm not sure what more information could be given.
        ANSWER: Nothing.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  All the information we need is here.
    QUESTION 1 To what does the pp.2212-2295 refer?
        ANSWER: It refers to a quotation in the text.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  We'd need one page reference for that (no quote could be 83 pages long), and this would appear in a footnote.
        ANSWER: It refers to the number of pages of Alexander Pope in the Norton Anthology.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  With an anthologised poet, it is correct to put in the number of pages he or she takes up in the bigger book.
