        ANSWER: Hi!
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        ANSWER: Hello,
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        ANSWER: Dear Ann Hammond,
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        ANSWER: Dear Mrs. Hammond,
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  Mrs. Hammond has given you her title, so you should use it.
    QUESTION 1 There are contractions, e.g. you'll need, in the advertisement.  Should you use contractions in your reply?
