    Writing activity 14. Proof reading
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO  <font size="4">From a CV:<br /><br />Skills Developed: MS word; Adobe Photoshop; Macromedia Dreamweaver; Professional communication and Project management skills; working as part of a team.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Three words in this text are wrongly capitalised.  What are they?
        ANSWER: Word, photoshop and dreamweaver
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  These are all proper names, i.e. the names of products, so should be capitalised.
        ANSWER: Developed, Professional and Project
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  These are just an ordinary verb (developed), an ordinary adjective (professional) and an ordinary noun (project), so none of them needs a capital.
