<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4" style="font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Read the following essay title and then the concluding line(s) that are offered. Choose the concluding line(s) you think best. Each selection has an explanation, so even if your choice agrees with ours, it is worth browsing through them all.</font><o:p></o:p></p> <!--EndFragment--> 
        ANSWER: Therefore, it is impossible to say what was the most important factor in the development of knightly ethos in eleventh and twelfth century Europe.
        FEEDBACK: Endings like this are not wrong, but they are unsatisfactory, and tend to leave the marker feeling that you haven't thought hard enough about the subject.  Having done your research and written your essay, you should have some view.  This is not a good option.  
        ANSWER: So, all in all, I think the development of romance was really important for the development of knightly ethos.  
        FEEDBACK: The idea behind this line is fine, but the line itself is too informal for an academic essay.   It might read better as:  In conclusion, courtly love seems the most important factor in the development of knightly ethos in eleventh and twelfth century Europe.
        ANSWER: Thus it would seem that from the three factors identified at the beginning of this essay as essential to the development of knightly ethos in eleventh and twelfth century  Europe, the church emerges as the major one.
        FEEDBACK: This does the job of a concluding line perfectly professionally.   The essay topics are referred to but not listed and a view is taken.  This is the best option of the three offered here.
