<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4" style="font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Read the following essay title and then the concluding line(s) that are offered. Choose the concluding line(s) you think best. Each selection has an explanation, so even if your choice agrees with ours, it is worth browsing through them all.</font><o:p></o:p></p> <!--EndFragment--> 
        ANSWER: The crown was evidently far stronger in 1625 than it had been in 1567, yet as Julian Goodare argues, there appear to be few tangible developments in the governance of Scotland that are the direct consequence of union. (reference)   It is difficult to argue, therefore, that the union of the crowns made it easier for a Scottish monarch to govern the Scottish realm.  Indeed, as this essay has shown, union simply produced a whole new set of difficulties to which, when absenteeism was added, a British monarch had to attempt to find a new set of solutions. 
        FEEDBACK: These lines reflect the title of the essay and bring a sense of positive closure.  The reference is cleverly placed to add weight to the essay at this final stage.  This is the best option.
        ANSWER: As James was both king of Scotland and England, it is difficult to measure the ease of his rule over the Scottish realm in comparison with other monarchs. He just had to try and make it work.
        FEEDBACK: These concluding lines sit firmly on the fence.  The essay writer seems to have concluded nothing, which is a shame.  These lines are not the best option.
        ANSWER: James VI and 1's decisions proved both popular and unpopular, making his rule both easier and more difficult.  His absence from Scotland was unpopular.  His promise not to make changes gained him respect. The union of the crowns could, therefore, be said to have made his rule over the realm both easier and more difficult.
        FEEDBACK: These concluding lines are a complete fudge.  The writer needs to take a stance one way or the other.  These lines would irritate a marker no end.
