<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="4" style="font-family: trebuchet ms,verdana,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Read the following essay title and then the concluding line(s) that are offered. Choose the concluding line(s) you think best. Each selection has an explanation, so even if your choice agrees with ours, it is worth browsing through them all.</font><o:p></o:p></p> <!--EndFragment--> 
        ANSWER: As this essay has shown, therefore, the creation of the burghs and the trade this encouraged was not only responsible for the emergence of the middling sorts, it was integral to the shaping of Scotland itself.
        FEEDBACK: This has a nice 'wrapped up' feel to it, making a big statement which leaves the reader satisfied.  This is the best option.
        ANSWER: Burgh-based trade led to political stability, allowing the middling sorts to urbanise, it lead to economic stability which provided the middling sorts with numerous monetary advantages like jobs, currency and increased domestic and international trade, and finally burgh-based trade led to the consolidation of royal authority which aided in creating a common Scottish identity and consciousness for a growing middle sorts social group.
        FEEDBACK: First of all, this sentence is far, far too long.  It would be much better split into at least three small sentences.  Secondly, concluding lines draw arguments together but shouldn't simply repeat them.  Sometimes, recapitulation is good, to remind the reader of the main points of the essay.  But recapitulation should never turn into a sentence like this.  This is not a good choice. 
        ANSWER: The middling sorts were predominantly traders.  Therefore the growth of burgh-based trade was quite important in the creation of this new social group.
        FEEDBACK: These lines are very plodding, and the inclusion of the word 'quite' leaves the reader feeling that the writer is sitting on the fence.  Be bold.  Take a stance and finish with a carefully considered flourish.
    Writing activity 25. Structure - linking lines
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">Cash replaced the old bartering system, and by 1250, mints had been established in burghs all over the kingdom. The amount of sterling produced in Scotland doubled around the period of the creation of the burghs. </font> 
    QUESTION 0  <link rel="File-List" href="file://localhost/Users/katiegrant/Library/Caches/TemporaryItems/msoclip1/01/clip_filelist.xml" /><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> Normal 0 0 1 23 132 1 1 162 11.1282 </xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml> 0 0 0 </xml><![endif]--><style>&lt;!-- /* Font Definitions */@font-face {font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; panose-1:0 2 2 6 3 5 4 5 2 3; mso-font-charset:0; mso-generic-font-family:auto; mso-font-pitch:variable; mso-font-signature:50331648 0 0 0 1 0;} /* Style Definitions */p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; margin:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt; mso-pagination:widow-orphan; font-size:12.0pt; font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;; mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;}table.MsoNormalTable {mso-style-parent:&quot;&quot;; font-size:10.0pt; font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;}@page Section1 {size:612.0pt 792.0pt; margin:72.0pt 90.0pt 72.0pt 90.0pt; mso-header-margin:36.0pt; mso-footer-margin:36.0pt; mso-paper-source:0;}div.Section1 {page:Section1;}--&gt;</style><!--StartFragment-->
<p> <font size="4">The example shows the final line(s) of a paragraph. Read the line(s), and then, from the options offered, choose the one you think is the best link to the next paragraph. All the options have explanations, so even if you find our preferred option quickly, it's worth browsing through the others. </font></p><!--EndFragment--> 
        ANSWER: International trade was something else that increased when the burghs were created.
        FEEDBACK: This is a good linking sentence, reflecting the theme of the previous paragraph.  The use of the word 'also' makes the paragraph transition smooth.
        ANSWER: It is believed that the earliest burghs were created during the reign of King David 1.
        FEEDBACK: This does link with the previous paragraph, in that both talk about the creation of the burghs. However, this sentence seems in the wrong place.  It feels as though it should have come at the beginning of the essay, not in the middle of a detailed discussion about cash and mints.
        ANSWER: The middling sorts began to take up influential positions in the law and the kirk.
        FEEDBACK: This sentence doesn't create a natural bridge between the paragraphs.   The reader is jolted into the new topic, which is never a good thing.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">During the rein of James IV, the hall of Stirling Castle was designed and the royal palace of Holyrood built. Developments in the visual arts were<font size="4"> </font></font><font size="4">instigated when liturgical books were imported from the Netherlands.</font><br />
