        FEEDBACK: I'm afraid it always matters.  This is not to irritate, but to make sure that citations can easily be checked.
    QUESTION 1 Which of the following is the correct formatting for this footnote?
        ANSWER: 1 G. W. S. Barrow, Robert Bruce 4th edn, (Edinburgh: Edinburgh University Press, 2005), p.71
        FEEDBACK: All is correct here, except for the title of the book, Robert Bruce, which should be italicised.
        ANSWER: 1 Barrow, G. W. S., ROBERT BRUCE, Edition 4, p.71, Edinburgh University Press.
        FEEDBACK: Almost everything here is incorrect.  In a footnote, the first name, or initials, of the author should come first.  A book title should never be wholly capitalised;  it should be italicised.  The edition number is shortened to 4th edn.;  we need the place of publication, publisher and date of publication in brackets, followed by the page number of the quotation.
