INTRO  <font size="4">One of the few capable officials left to govern Scotland, Alexander Seton, voiced his complaints in a letter in which he asked James &quot;to follow the rules laid down for the filling of vacancies and not permit resignation in favorem if, as many people supposed 'your majesty is to retain some of our number.' &quot; <sup>9</sup> <br /><br /></font> 
