    Writing activity 17. Sentence fragments
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <font size="4">1. This affected his ability to compose. <br />2. Although it did not stop him composing more works.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 <font size="4">Which is the complete sentence and which is the sentence fragment? </font>
        ANSWER: 1. is the fragment and 2. is the complete sentence.
        FEEDBACK: No, that's not right.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 1. is the whole sentence and 2. is the fragment.
        FEEDBACK: That's correct.  1. has a subject - this - and a driving verb - affected.  2. is a sub-clause: it adds information but does not have a driving verb.   Most groups of words starting with 'although' are sub-clauses, not complete sentences.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
INTRO <font size="4">1. Despite his great need of money - he was often in debt and was no stranger at the pawn shop. <br />2. Mozart resigned.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Which is the complete sentence and which the fragment?
        ANSWER: 1. is the complete sentence and 2. is the fragment. 
        FEEDBACK: No, that's not right.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 1. is the fragment and 2. is the complete sentence.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  Groups of words that start 'Despite' are usually sub-clauses, i.e. they add to or qualify information, but do not constitute a whole sentence.  2. is a whole sentence: it has a subject - Mozart - and a driving verb - resigned.  That's all a complete sentence needs.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">1. There are a number of theories relevant to the question.<br />2. One being put forward by Hanslick and another by Madell.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Which is the complete sentence and which the sentence fragment?
        ANSWER: 1. is the complete sentence and 2. is the sentence fragment.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  1. has a subject and driving verb - there are.  2. has no driving verb, i.e. no verb that sets the action in space or time, so the sentence makes no sense on its own. 
        ANSWER: 1. is the fragment and 2. is the complete sentence.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
INTRO <font size="4">1. Sound recording added a new dimension.<br />2. Influencing composers, performers and producers in equal measure as they saw the potential of this new medium.</font><br /> 
    QUESTION 0 Which is the complete sentence and which the sentence fragment?
        ANSWER: 1. is the complete sentence and 2. is the fragment.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  1. has a subject - sound recording - and a driving verb - added.  2. has no driving verb.  'Influencing' does not set the sentence in time, so the sentence is left hanging in the air.  If you join up 1. and 2., then 2. becomes a whole sentence.
        ANSWER: 1. is the fragment and 2. the complete sentence.
        FEEDBACK: No, that's not right.  Try again.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">1. As the music not only makes the story told by the narrator more dramatic, it also supports the singer.<br />2. The orchestration matters. </font> 
    QUESTION 0 Which of these is a complete sentence and which is just a fragment?
        ANSWER: 1. is a complete sentence and 2. is a fragment.
        FEEDBACK: That's not right.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 1. is a sentence fragment and 2. is a complete sentence.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  1. is longer, but it does not contain a driving verb, so is a sub-clause.  'As' often introduces a qualifying sub-clause, and does in this case.  2. has a subject - the orchestra - and a driving verb - matters - so, though short, is a complete sentence.
