lic;">Mozartiana</span>, <span style="font-style: italic;">Capriccio Italien</span>, a Violin Concerto, the <span style="font-style: italic;">Manfred </span>symphony in B minor, and an Overture in E minor entitled <span style="font-style: italic;">The Storm</span>. </font> 
    QUESTION 0 Which of the three texts is properly formatted?
        ANSWER: 1.
        FEEDBACK: Not 1.  Try again.
        ANSWER: 2.
        FEEDBACK: Well done. 2 is correct.  Generic titles, e.g. Symphony No. X, are not italicised.  Works with specific names are italicised, although not nicknames, e.g. 'Manfred', which are placed in inverted commas.  Titles need appropriate capitals.  Ballet titles are italicised. 
