INTRO <font size="4">The pressure exerted on the tissues also prevents the lymphatic system from functioning properly, for example it is unable to remove waste products. If the pressure continues then the tissues become ischemic and eventually die, causing areas of damage to the skin (Waterlow, 2005). Shearing of the tissues,when combined with pressure, can also be responsible for causing pressure ulcers. Shear occurs when the person's body weight is combined with the already existing pressure, so that when the person tries to move part of their body, the skin remains fixed. </font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is this text fine as one paragraph?
        ANSWER: No.  It should be divided into two.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.
        ANSWER: Yes.  It's fine as one paragraph.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  I think it should be divided into two.
    QUESTION 1 If you think it should be divided, where should the new paragraph start and why?
        ANSWER: The last sentence should be the start of a new paragraph.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again!
        ANSWER: 'Shearing of the tissues' should open a new paragraph.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  Shearing is a new theme, and new themes should have paragraphs of their own.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
