    QUESTION 0 This text contains three themes.  Are they properly divided up into paragraphs?
        ANSWER: Yes.  Each theme needs a separate paragraph.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree. Themes should be divided into paragraphs, but there's a difference between a theme and a list.  This is a list of risk factors.  To make a paragraph, each item on the list would need more information attached.
        ANSWER: No.  We don't need all these paragraphs.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  Themes should be divided into paragraphs, but there's a difference between a theme and a list.  This is a list of risk factors.  To make a paragraph, each item on the list would need more information attached.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">A chest drain and attachment to an underwater seal system will have been selected as a mode of treatment in order to help restore the normal expansion and function of the lungs. This is done by removing air, blood, pus or fluid from the pleural space (Hyde et al. 1997, cited in Dougherty &amp; Lister 2008: 497). The nurse will be responsible for the maintenance of the chest drain. The main objectives of care are to keep the system patent, maintain sterility of the drainage system, infection control and to ensure the system remains upright and airtight (Kirkwood 2002, cited in Dougherty &amp; Lister, 2008). The nursing process is a four-staged system that allows the nurse to tailor care to each patient. It was formally incorporated into nurse training by the General Nursing Council in the UK in 1977 (Hogston &amp; Marjoram 2007). The four stages are assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Into how many paragraphs would you divide this text?
        ANSWER: Leave it at one.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again!
        ANSWER: Into two paragraphs.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.
