INTRO <font size="4">Graduate Diploma assignment title:<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Lymphoedema Assessment and Management</span><br /><br />Which of the following is the best first line for the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Introduction</span>?<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0  <font size="4">Read the essay title and the opening lines. Which opening lines are the best option? All the choices have explanations, so even if your first choice agrees with ours, it's worth clicking on all the options.</font> 
        ANSWER: For the purposes of this assignment, the intention is to discuss then analyse a holistic assessment which was carried out on a patient with her consent.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  This opening line is full of superfluous words.  What value do the phrases 'for the purposes of this assignment and 'the intention is' add?  Keep your opening lines crisp and to the point.  This is not a good choice. 
        ANSWER: Lymphoedema is defined as an 'accumulation of lymph, producing subcutaneous tissues swelling'.
        FEEDBACK: This isn't a bad choice, but it is missing a reference.  Never quote without giving the appropriate reference.
        ANSWER: Tortora and Grabowski (2000:770) define lymphoedema as an 'accumulation of lymph, producing subcutaneous tissue swelling'.
        FEEDBACK: This is a good choice.  Here, we have facts and a reference.  It doesn't get much better than that!
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO <font size="4">Graduate Diploma assignment title:<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Lymphoedema Assessment and Management</span><br /><br />Which of the following is the best first line for the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Conclusion</span>?</font> 
    QUESTION 0  <font size="4">Read the essay title and the opening lines. Which opening lines are the best option? All the choices have explanations, so even if your first choice agrees with ours, it's worth clicking on all the options.</font> 
        ANSWER: This assignment has reviewed the literature on the management of lymphoedema.
        FEEDBACK: This is a statement of the obvious, so not the best choice.
        ANSWER: As has been shown, the literature on lymphoedema management is conflicting, but the four cornerstones as outlined in the document Best Practice for the Management of Lymphoedema (Lymphoedema Framework 2006) remain the basis for all current treatment.
        FEEDBACK: This line sounds informative and professional.  There are no wasted words and it contains a good reference.  This is an excellent option.
        ANSWER: Compression garments have mixed results in research.
        FEEDBACK: A reader is jolted if a section begins with a sentence on a particular aspect of treatment rather than a more over-arching point.  Begin with the general and move to the particular, not the other way round.  This isn't the best choice.
