INTRO  <font size="4" style="font-weight: bold;">Research module assignment title: </font><br /><br /><font size="4">Patients' experiences of attending a palliative daycare centre.</font><br /><br />Palliative daycare is the fastest growing but least researched area of palliative care (Myers &amp; Hearn, 2001). Common themes in research are patients feeling relaxed and comfortable in the daycare setting <style>@font-face { font-family: &quot;Cambria&quot;;}p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal { margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; }div.Section1 { page: Section1; }</style> but more research is needed to identify the particular qualities ofdaycare centres that produce these feelings. In a study of five palliative care day centres in the London region, two models were identified: social, and medical. The study involved interviewing new referrals to the 'social' daycare service three times over a three month period to assess if themes identified changed over time. The number of patients able to take part in the study did not remain stable.<br /> 
    QUESTION 0 How many themes does this paragraph address?
        ANSWER: One.  It's all about palliative daycare.
        FEEDBACK: That's the general heading, I agree.  But several themes emerge.
        ANSWER: Two.  Palliative daycare and a particular study.
        FEEDBACK: These themes are certainly incorporated, but it seems to me that the paragraph skips about, and more themes are addressed.
