    Writing activity 18. Introduction
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <font size="4">Can you answer the following question(s)?</font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is the introduction the same as an abstract, only a little longer?
        ANSWER: Yes.
        FEEDBACK: I'm afraid that's not right.
        ANSWER: No.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  An abstract and an introduction have two different functions.  An abstract is an overview of your entire dissertation or project.  An introduction sets the scene for your topic in detail.
    QUESTION 1 How long should the introduction be?
        ANSWER: One paragraph.
        FEEDBACK: It might be, but that would be unusual.  An introduction might be over a page long - long enough to perform all its functions.
        ANSWER: Two paragraphs at most.
        FEEDBACK: It might be two paragraphs, but not two AT MOST since an introduction must be long enough to perform all its functions.
        ANSWER: As long as it needs to be.
        FEEDBACK: That's right.  An introduction might be over a page long.  The important thing is that it performs all its functions.
    QUESTION 2 From the following, pick out the three functions of an introduction.
        ANSWER: To set the scene for the dissertation or project.
        FEEDBACK: Well done.  That's one function.  
        ANSWER: To say why the topic appeals to you personally.
        FEEDBACK: No, that's not a function of an introduction to an academic text.
        ANSWER: To give a complete history of the topic.
        FEEDBACK: No, not a complete history.  You need to place your particular dissertation or project in context and this may involve some history, but don't go back to the year dot.
        ANSWER: To explain why the topic is worth investigating.
        FEEDBACK: Yes.  This is a very important aspect of your introduction.
        ANSWER: To describe in detail any literature you're going to critique.
        FEEDBACK: Yes.  The introduction is the right place to do this.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
