    QUESTION 0  <font size="4">Read the text then answer the question(s).</font> 
        ANSWER: This study looks at what are claimed to be the deteriorating experiences and perceptions of patients and medical staff in Emergency Departments (EDs) since the four hour target in waiting times was introduced. 
        FEEDBACK: I'd say this was better for the abstract since it identifies the nature of and reason for the study.
        ANSWER: Waiting times in Accident and Emergency departments have historically been long with UK struggling to cope with high demand and poor patient flow (Royal College of Nursing (RCN) 2008).
        FEEDBACK: I'd say this was suitable for the introduction since this line sets the scene for the topic.  Setting the scene is a function of the introduction, not the abstract.
