    Writing activity 03. Theory, apparatus, method
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 2
INTRO  <font size="4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Apparatus:</span><br /><br />Three flasks were used. All three were filled with boiled water and sealed with a thermometer placed inside.</font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is there anything missing from this apparatus description?
        ANSWER: No, there's nothing missing.  It's a good description.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Not only are there things missing, but it's also a little ambiguous.  Read quickly, it seems that the thermometer was part of the sealing process.  Any description in physics needs to be absolutely clear.  Try this:  Three flasks were used: one silver, one white and one black. All three were filled with 300ml of boiled water from the kettle.  After placing a thermometer inside, each flask was sealed. 
        ANSWER: Yes, there are things missing.  This description needs more detail.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  Not only are there things missing, but it's also a little ambiguous.  Read quickly, it seems that the thermometer was part of the sealing process.  Any description in physics needs to be absolutely clear.  This is better:  Three flasks were used: one silver, one white and one black. All three were filled with 300ml of boiled water (give temperature) from the kettle.  After placing a thermometer inside, each flask was sealed.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <font size="4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Method:</span><br /><br />The thermometer was used to record the temperature. All the flasks lost heat at different rates. This was recorded.</font> 
    QUESTION 0 What is missing from this method description?
        ANSWER: Nothing.  It tells the reader everything the reader needs to know.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  The reader needs to know how often the temperature was taken.  Also, were all the flasks the same?  How were the results recorded?  Go through the experiment step by step so that nothing is left out of your method description. 
        ANSWER: There's too little detail in this description.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  The reader needs to know how often the temperature was taken.  Also, were all the flasks the same?  How were the results recorded?  Go through the experiment step by step so that nothing is left out of your method description.
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 3
INTRO <font size="4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Apparatus:</span><br /><br />Lenses of different focal lengths; plane mirror; convex mirror; optical bench; triangular light source; lens holder; mirror holder; ruler.<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is this a good example of the apparatus section?
        ANSWER: Yes.  It's clear and comprehensive.
        FEEDBACK: The content is fine, but in a report the apparatus should be described in prose, not simply listed.  It should have read something like:  The apparatus used for this experiment comprised lenses of different focal lengths placed in lense holders and set in front of mirrors, one plain and one convex.  A triangular light source was used to create an image on a screen (Fig. 1).
        ANSWER: No, it's not a good example.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  The content is fine, but in a report the apparatus should be described in prose, not simply listed.  It should have read something like:  The apparatus used for this experiment comprised lenses of different focal lengths placed in lense holders and set in front of mirrors, one plain and one convex.  A triangular light source was used to create an image on a screen (Fig. 1).
