        ANSWER: It's not detailed enough.
        FEEDBACK: You're right, it's not.  But that's not the main problem.  The main problem is that it's written as a set of instructions rather than an account of what was done.  A method section is not like a cooking recipe, telling the reader what to do.  A method section is an account, telling the reader what was done and why.
