INTRO  <font size="4"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Critical Review title:</span><br /><br />Does alcohol have an impact on neuropsychological function?</font><br /> 
    QUESTION 0 Remember:  these are the opening lines of the abstract (i.e. NOT the introduction or the main body of the text).
        ANSWER: The impact of alcohol on cognitive function matters because of the impact of binge drinking on western societies.  This Review reviews four key papers with reference to two specific experimental designs: cognitive studies; and brain imaging studies.
        FEEDBACK: Clear and informative.   These opening lines bode well for the remainder of the abstract.  An excellent option.
        ANSWER: The impact of alcohol on cognitive function matters because of the impact of binge drinking on western societies.  Our alcohol consumption severely stretches our criminal justice system and has detrimental effects on family life.  In Scotland alone, 47% of violent crime is alcohol related (Scottish Crime and Justice Survey, 2008-09). 
        FEEDBACK: The facts about crime and alcohol may be correct, but if thought relevant to this paper, should be placed in the introduction.  The abstract is an overview of this paper.  That's its function.  Not a good option.
        ANSWER: The impact of alcohol on cognitive function matters because of the impact of binge drinking on western societies.  This paper will look at several areas of neuropsychological function including pre-natal exposure, exposure in adolescence and gender difference.  Finally, it will assess what we can learn from these areas.
        FEEDBACK: These lines read like the opening lines of an essay.  The abstract is a complete overview of the Critical Review.  It does not tell us what you WILL look at, but what you HAVE looked at, and what your conclusions are.  Not the best option.
