INTRO <font size="4">Essay title:<br /><br />Is mirror therapy an effective treatment of phantom limb pain?<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0  <font size="4">Read the essay title, then choose which you think are the best concluding lines. Every choice has an explanation, so even if you choose correctly first time, it's worth skimming through them all.</font> 
        ANSWER: Through the work of Ramachandran and others, it cannot be doubted that mirror therapy is effective in treating phantom limb pain.  However, the small sample size used prohibits mirror therapy being hailed as the ultimate treatment.  Future trials look set to remedy this current lack of data, and if these trials prove as successful as all previous trials, mirror therapy looks set to be the therapy of choice for all those suffering phantom limb pain.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  This sums up clearly and succinctly, and answers the question.  What more do you want from concluding lines!
        ANSWER: Phantom limb pain is really terrible for sufferers.  Mirror therapy has received a great deal of clinical and scientific attention in academic publications and seems set to be the therapy of the future.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Although perfectly readable, these lines are vague and unspecific.  The phrase 'really terrible' has no place in an academic essay.  Good concluding lines for an academic essay should leave the reader confident of the writer's authority.  I don't think these lines achieve that.  
