        Task selectcat difficulty 2
        Task selectcat difficulty 2
        Task multiplechoice difficulty 1
INTRO <ol> 
  <li><font size="4">An abstract can be as long as you like.</font></li> 
  <li><font size="4">An abstract sets the scene for your Critical Review.</font></li> 
  <li><font size="4">Your abstract is the most important paragraph in your Critical Review.</font></li> 
  <li><font size="4">You must write your abstract first.</font></li> 
  <li><font size="4">An abstract is not essential: you can write one if you want to, but it's up to you.</font></li> 
</ol><font size="4"><br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 Is statement 1 true or false?
        ANSWER: True.
        FEEDBACK: No, it's not true.  Abstracts are often word-limited.  Check your assignment details.  Traditionally, they are one succinct paragraph, or at the most two.  They are brief a brief overview, to allow the reader to see if the Critical Review contains information they are looking for.
        ANSWER: False.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  Abstracts are often word-limited.  Check your assignment details.  Traditionally, they are one succinct paragraph, or at the most two.  They are a brief overview, to allow the reader to see if the Critical Review contains the information they are looking for.
    QUESTION 1 Is statement 2 true or false?
        ANSWER: True.
