INTRO  <font size="4">A (repeated measures) ANOVA compared ASC scores for low, medium and high levels of exam anxiety and revealed a significant main effect of exam anxiety F(2,88)=10.77, <span style="font-style: italic;">p</span>&lt;.0001.</font> 
    QUESTION 0 What kind of an ANOVA is this?
        ANSWER: A two way ANOVA.
        FEEDBACK: No, not a two way ANOVA.  Try again.
        ANSWER: A one way ANOVA.
        FEEDBACK: Correct.
    QUESTION 1 If you feel the description is lacking, which of the following might be a good way to complete it?
        ANSWER: Planned contrasts revealed that those with low levels of exam anxiety scored higher on ASC than those with medium and high levels of exam anxiety, t(44)=3.38, p<.001.  Mean ASC scores for low, medium and high levels of anxiety are shown in Table 1 and Figure 1.
        FEEDBACK: This is excellent, giving all the information we need, including the probability associated with the statistics.
        ANSWER: Mean ASC scores for low, medium and high levels of anxiety are shown in Table 1 and Figure 1.
        FEEDBACK: We need to know what the planned contrasts were, as well as the mean ASC scores.
