INTRO  <font size="4">Abstract</font><font size="4"><br /> <br /> 1. Significant findings were that pet-owners scored significantly higher than non pet-owners on the Anthropomorphism Scale; and that there was a significant gender difference.</font><font size="4"><br /> 2. Two scales were used: the Anthropomorphism Scale Interview (Albert &amp; Bulcroft, 1988) and the Belief in Paranormal Scale (Jones, Russell &amp; Nickell, 1977). <br /> </font><font size="4">3. The validity of the anthropomorphism scale used was questionable.</font><font size="4"><br /> 4. The results will find no significant correlation between these scales.</font><br /> <font size="4">5. This study will aim to investigate whether a correlation exists between paranormal beliefs and anthropomorphism of animals.</font><font size="4"><br /> <br /> </font> 
    QUESTION 0 Sentences 1 and 2 are written in the past tense; Sentences 4 and 5 in the future. Which is correct? 
        ANSWER: Future.  The reader has not yet read the full report.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        ANSWER: It doesn't matter.  Tense is a matter of choice.
        FEEDBACK: I disagree.  Try again.
        ANSWER: Past.  The abstract is an overview of the entire report, showing what the writer has discovered.
        FEEDBACK: I agree.  Can't really be in the future when it's reporting the results.
