INTRO <font size="4">Trilobites can be divided into three main parts; the cephalon; the thorax; and the pygidium.</font> 
    QUESTION 0 One of these semi-colons should be a colon.  Which one is it?
        ANSWER: The semi-colon after parts?
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  A colon introduces a list, not a semi-colon.  A semi-colon can be used to separate items in a list.
        ANSWER: The semi-colon after cephalon.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. The colon should come after parts.  A colon introduces a list, not a semi-colon.  A semi-colon can be used to separate items in a list.
        ANSWER: The semi-colon after thorax.
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect. The colon should come after parts, since a colon introduces a list, not a semi-colon.  A semi-colon can be used to separate items in a list.
