INTRO <font size="4">Other signals of the presence of magma under the ocean surface are the &quot;black smokers&quot; which are released by vents expelling hot mineral water.<br /><br />&quot;As soon as it forms, new oceanic crust moves away from the ridge axis, and as this happens, more magma rises from below, so still more crust forms.&quot; (Marshak, 2005). &quot;As the newly formed oceanic crust moves away from the ridge axis, the crust and the uppermost mantle directly beneath it gradually cool as they lose heat to the ocean above. As soon as the mantle rock cools below 1280 degrees, it becomes, by definition, part of the lithosphere&quot; (Marshak, 2005).<br /></font> 
    QUESTION 0 There are three quotations in this text.  One is correctly used.  Which one is it?
        ANSWER: "black smokers"
        FEEDBACK: Correct.  This is a small quotation, just using the accepted name for the plumes of hot, mineral-laden water that spout through hydrothermal vents.
        ANSWER: "As soon as it forms ... crust forms"
        FEEDBACK: Incorrect.  This quotation is much too long.  We need to see explanations in your own words.  Copying chunks from books, even when properly acknowledged, is not acceptable. 
