        FEEDBACK: Correct.  There are just too many quotations.  You need to pick one only for this paragraph.
        ANSWER: Yes.  Using Mill's words will always add to our understanding.
        FEEDBACK: No, this isn't right.  Careful use of Mill's words would help, but this example shows that when quotations are piled up, it is hard to distinguish between them.  Too many quotations, like to many anything, devalue a text rather than adding weight.
